                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d357">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">638.6531/12: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Woodward</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-09-21T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 21, 1934—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>79. Your 100, September 14, 2 p.m. Your actions approved. However, you should
                    make it perfectly clear that this Government expects any reduction on any
                    Italian product to be extended to the like product of the United States.<note
                        n="51" xml:id="d357fn51">However, the negotiations did not result in the
                        signature of a commercial arrangement between Haiti and Italy at this
                        time.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
